\f1\b \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Key Strengths
\f0\b0 : It introduces 
\f1\b native Actions
\f0\b0  to drastically reduce form boilerplate, eliminating manual loading and error states. Features like the 
\f2\fs28 use
\f0\fs32  hook streamline resource and context consumption, while native support for ref-passing directly via props simplifies code structures. It also forms the operational foundation for modern full-stack architectures like React Server Components (RSCs). [{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://react.dev/blog/2024/12/05/react-19"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 \ul \ulc3 1}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/reactjs/react-19-new-features-and-updates/"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 \ul \ulc3 2}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://dev.to/mridudixit15/react-19-new-features-explained-with-examples-2f7o"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 \ul \ulc3 3}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://medium.com/@Brilworks/the-future-of-react-js-trends-and-predictions-for-2025-9264881bf572"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 \ul \ulc3 4}}]\
