\f1\b\fs32 \cf0 3. Radix UI (The Accessibility Engine) [{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://medium.com/@the.sikandar.dev/introduction-to-shadcn-ui-build-beautiful-accessible-react-components-46dfa3474295"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 \ul \ulc3 1}}]\

\f0\b0 Radix UI provides unstyled, "headless" primitive components (like dropdowns, dialogs, sliders, and accordions). [{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.linkedin.com/pulse/shadcn-ui-beginners-delwo-athauda-tjfyc"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 \ul \ulc3 1}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.greatfrontend.com/blog/latest"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 \ul \ulc3 2}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://clay.global/blog/web-design-guide/top-css-frameworks"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 \ul \ulc3 3}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://dev.to/riteshkokam/5-react-ui-component-libraries-for-your-next-project-2hn2"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 \ul \ulc3 4}}]\
